Low FODMAP diet: A diet that restricts the intake of fermentable oligo-, di-, and mono-saccharides, and polyols, often recommended for managing irritable bowel syndrome (IBS) symptoms; 
Pain intensity: A measure of how severe pain is perceived by an individual, commonly assessed using numeric pain scales or similar tools; 
Control group: In research, a group that does not receive the treatment being tested, used as a baseline to compare against the treatment group.
